<item>
            <title>[PIG-4027] Always check for latest Tez snapshot dependencies</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4027</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ivy resolver for apache-snapshots sets &lt;tt&gt;checkModified=&quot;true&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; which updates the metadata of Tez dependencies if there are modifications, but since the intermediary Tez builds are published under the same revision (0.5.0-incubating-SNAPSHOT) the local cache will only be populated for the first time with the jars and it won&apos;t get updated afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to force ivy to always look up the repository whether there are changes in the Tez snapshots jars, &lt;tt&gt;changing=&quot;true&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; should be set on the Tez dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remark: when Tez dependencies are bumped up to a stable release, this flag needs to be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
